# deploy/secrets/platform-sms.env
# Outbound phone verification-code credentials — Aliyun Number Authentication
# Service (号码认证服务, PNVS / Dypnsapi). Do not commit real values.
#
# compose.platform.yml injects this file only into containers that send phone
# verification codes (currently auth-bff, the IdP phone-code sender). Do not
# duplicate ALIYUN_SMS_* in .env.<service> files. When the four required values
# are unset, @vxture/service-sms falls back to console.log + a fixed dev code
# (no real send) — set real values for production phone-code login.
#
# The RAM AccessKey must be granted Dypnsapi permission (e.g. AliyunDypnsFullAccess);
# create one under RAM 访问控制 → 用户 if none exists. SignName/TemplateCode are the
# preset public values from the Number Authentication Service console (短信验证码 /
# 个人开发者免资质) — not secret. Preset templates 100001–100005 each carry two
# variables ${code} and ${min}; @vxture/service-sms fills ##code## (Aliyun generates
# the code) and ${min} (= ALIYUN_SMS_VALID_SECONDS / 60).
#
# Templates: 100001 登录/注册 · 100002 修改绑定手机号 · 100003 重置密码 ·
# 100004 绑定新手机号 · 100005 验证绑定手机号. We use 100001 for every send today
# (single /auth/send-phone-code entry covers login + social bind-phone), and
# CheckSmsVerifyCode is template-agnostic so one template covers verification too.

# Required (AccessKey is account-specific; sign/template are the shared presets)
ALIYUN_SMS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=CHANGEME
ALIYUN_SMS_ACCESS_KEY_SECRET=CHANGEME
ALIYUN_SMS_SIGN_NAME=速通互联验证码
ALIYUN_SMS_TEMPLATE_CODE=100001

# Optional (defaults: code length 6 to match the frontend, 300s validity)
# ALIYUN_SMS_SCHEME_NAME=default
# ALIYUN_SMS_CODE_LENGTH=6
# ALIYUN_SMS_VALID_SECONDS=300
